In this video, we are going to learn about metaphors.

00:03.377 --> 00:05.102
That's a fun word to say, isn't it?

00:05.314 --> 00:06.007
Metaphors.

00:06.143 --> 00:10.523
You're going to understand what metaphors are and how to use them.

00:12.948 --> 00:15.623
First, what is a metaphor?

00:15.855 --> 00:17.991
What is a metaphor?

00:20.755 --> 00:24.471
Well, a metaphor is a way of comparing two things.

00:24.596 --> 00:27.236
It's not the only way to compare two things,...

00:27.571 --> 00:33.309
...but it's a very interesting and creative way of comparing two things.

00:35.561 --> 00:40.319
You might have seen examples of metaphors in books and in poetry,...

00:42.458 --> 00:47.525
...and there's a really big chance that you use metaphors in your everyday speeches.

